El Día de las Bibliotecas se celebra cad: Library Day has been celebrated every October 24 since 1997. This day was born as an initiative of the Spanish Association of Friends of Children's Books and Youth with the aim of raising awareness in society of the importance of reading and as a tribute and recognition of the work of librarians. This year's motto, For a sustainable future, aims to highlight the fundamental role played by all types of libraries (public, school, university, specialized and national/regional) in achieving the Sustainable Development Goals of the 2030 Agenda.
